\subsection{Correlation sensitivity (Model B)}
\label{sec:correlation-sensitivity}

The baseline bootstrap treats the FLAG/PDG mass uncertainties as uncorrelated Gaussians. Several quark mass determinations share lattice systematics, so this is an approximation. We test sensitivity using a common-correlation covariance matrix with off-diagonal element $\rho \cdot \sigma_i \sigma_j$ for $\rho \in \{0, 0.25, 0.50, 0.75\}$, with $\rho = 0.75$ chosen to bracket a pessimistic worst case, plus a structured covariance with $\rho = 0.5$ within $\{u,d,s\}$, $\rho = 0.1$ within $\{c,b,t\}$, and $\rho = 0.05$ across the two sectors.

